Herbs of European or North American origin ( Echinacea purpurea and Matricaria chamomilla) were more likely to be used by patients earning in excess of US $ 12, 000 per annum.
Garlic and Echinacea were the preferred herbal medicines in patients with more than twelve years formal education.
